modules.description: Converts between Cstruct buffers and IPv4 address representations. Parses 4-byte sequences into IPaddr.V4.t values and serializes IPaddr.V4.t instances into 4-byte Cstructs. Used to encode and decode IPv4 addresses in network protocols or binary data formats.

Converts between Cstruct buffers and IPv6 address representations. Parses 16-byte chunks from a Cstruct into an IPv6 address and serializes IPv6 addresses into 16-byte Cstructs. Used for network protocol encoding and decoding where raw byte representation is required.

Handles conversion and validation of IP addresses between string and binary formats, and parsing of MAC addresses from string representations. Operates on types such as IPv4, IPv6, and MAC address strings, with support for network byte order. Used to validate user input in network configuration tools and to parse device identifiers in packet analysis systems.

Converts between Cstruct buffers and both IPv4 and IPv6 address types, enabling low-level network data manipulation. Provides parsing and serialization functions for 4-byte and 16-byte representations of IP addresses. Allows encoding and decoding of IP addresses in binary formats, such as extracting an IPv4 address from a 4-byte buffer or generating a 16-byte Cstruct from an IPv6 address. Supports direct interaction with network protocols requiring raw byte-level handling of IP addresses.
